cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a framework for adversarially training generative models on composed data, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper focuses on improving the modularity, extensibility, and interpretability of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework is evaluated on two datasets in two different data modalities (image and text), which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Lastly, the paper derives sufficient conditions for the identifiability of compositional generative models, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
